    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/can-anyone-link-me-to-hana-db-sql-queries-documentation-or-guide/qaa-p/14112591#M4216899</id>
    <title>Re: Can anyone link me to Hana DB SQL queries documentati...</title>
    <updated>2025-05-27T12:55:23.291000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Vitaliy-R</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/183</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;SQL dialect differs between different databases of different vendors. SAP HANA's compliance with the mandatory features of the ANSI SQL/2016 standard:&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_HANA_PLATFORM/4fe29514fd584807ac9f2a04f6754767/09940a1ed38c4ceb80770632997b286b.html?locale=en-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_HANA_PLATFORM/4fe29514fd584807ac9f2a04f6754767/09940a1ed38c4ceb80770632997b286b.html?locale=en-US&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;In SAP HANA SQL, the DUMMY table is a special one-row, one-column table that is often used when a query requires a FROM clause but no actual table data is needed. It is similar to the DUAL table in Oracle. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Here are some common use cases for the DUMMY table:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;OL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Selecting a Constant Value&lt;/STRONG&gt;: When you want to return a constant value or perform a calculation that doesn't involve any table data, you can use the DUMMY table.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/OL&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-sql"&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT 'Hello, World!' AS greeting FROM DUMMY;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Calling Functions&lt;/STRONG&gt;: When you need to call a function that doesn't require any table data.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;DIV class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-sql"&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP AS now FROM DUMMY;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/can-anyone-link-me-to-hana-db-sql-queries-documentation-or-guide/qaa-p/14112591#M4216899"/>
    <published>2025-05-27T12:55:23.291000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
